The problem is that when you call `requestAnimationFrame` and pass it a reference to `move` as its callback, the `this` binding to your `Ball` instance is lost when the callback is executed. Instead, you must pass `move` in such a way that `this` is still bound to your `Ball` instance. You can do this by passing the function reference using the [`.bind()`][1] method, which takes an argument that specifies what the `this` binding will be when the callback function runs.

